name: Cos-ken

name: Otaku from the USA

name: Real Hard-Core

description: Proper Japanese Title: その先にあるもの… (Sono saki ni aru mono...)
name: What Lies Ahead...

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 信頼していた仲間の裏切りに際して勇者の取るべき行動 (Shinrai shite ita nakama no uragiri ni saishite yūsha no torubeki kōdō)

The party is victorious after a harsh battle, but the enemy's last spell hits Mage. Then Mage begins to scream about how she hates everyone and starts to attack the group. The battle takes an unexpected turn…
name: A Hero Betrayed Has But One Choice

description: Proper Japanese Title: 可児味噌
name: Kani Miso

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 脅迫状が来た日常 (Kyōhakujō ga Kita Nichijō)

Smith and Kimihito are on a date?! The monster girls borrow Suu's body to watch him, but when she becomes dehydrated she goes on a rampage. The monster girls fall one after another. Meanwhile, Smith and Kimihito move from location to location as they proceed with their date, eventually arriving at a love hotel?! Miia tries to enter the room, but Rachnera asks if she's prepared to witness Kimihito cheating on her...
name: Everyday Life with Threatening Letters

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 九号棟いたずら大好き (Kyū Gōtō Itazura Daisuki)

Haruki is on his guard against Uzuki's pranks, but is that was Uzuki is really planning?
name: Building Nine: For the Love of Pranks?!

description: Penguin is King of Gotham and after a shakeup at the GCPD, Detective James Gordon's moral compass wavers, as he seeks help from Penguin. Meanwhile, Bruce Wayne continues to explore the secrets from his father's office, while Gotham newcomers Theo Galavan (James Frain) and his sister, Tabitha (Jessica Lucas), make friends with some unlikely allies, a group of dangerous inmates from Arkham.
name: Damned if You Do...

description: Justine takes drastic measures to counter a surprise invasion. Nora and Fet perform a useful mission while Eph and Setrakian face off against an old foe.
name: The Battle For Red Hook

description: See what happens right after little Peter Quill is beamed aboard that Ravager spaceship.
name: Star-Lord: Part 1

description: Star-Lord's origin story continues when he meets Yondu and his band of alien pirates.
name: Star-Lord: Part 2

description: Meet the young sapling Groot, before he was Rocket's best bud.
name: Groot: Part 1

description: The inspirational tale of how young Groot becomes the last surviving member of his race.
name: Groot: Part 2

description: Follow Rocket's transformation from a simple creature into a brilliant, tech-savvy, trouble-maker.
name: Rocket Raccoon: Part 1

description: Rocket's story continues when he befriends the captive tree-creature, Groot.
name: Rocket Raccoon: Part 2

description: A galactic fighting superstar deals with his past, as he finds he must choose between revenge and doing the right thing.
name: Drax: Part 1

description: Drax's story continues when he finally confronts Ronan the Accuser.
name: Drax: Part 2

description: Gamora sets forth on a mission from Ronin to capture a mysterious artifact.
name: Gamora: Part 1

description: Gamora's loyalty is tested when she is given her first opportunity to choose a better path.
name: Gamora: Part 2

description: The newly christened Guardians of the Galaxy come into possession of a dangerous artifact that has Thanos' new second-in-charge, Korath, after them.
name: Road to Knowhere

description: Robin convinces the Titans to go back to school with him so he can finally become the all-American class president-type he's dreamed of being.
name: Hey You, Don't Neglect Me In Your Memory

series.name: My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 欲しいと願うアイテムこそなかなか手に入らない (Hoshī to negau aitemu koso nakanaka te ni hairanai)

The party enters a vast dungeon filled with powerful enemies, and their HP and MP are at their limits. Just as they're hoping to find a healing item, they find a treasure chest. But all the ones they've found so far have been trapped. What trap does this chest have?
name: You Don't Always Get What You Want or Need

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 十号棟 夢月お•ね•が•い (Jū Gōtō Mudzuki o• ne• ga• i)

Mutsuki has run into a problem she can't handle on her own. Is her request too much for Haruki to handle?
name: Building Ten: Mutsuki's Request?!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: Dのいる日常 (D no Iru Nichijō)

Kimihito and friends venture into the woods to barbecue at Papi's request. The forest is an illegal dumping ground for industrial waste. Suddenly, Kii the dryad, protector of the forest, appears. Kii ignores Papi's attempts to stop her and uses her tentacles to grasp Kimihito. Kii is a monster girl who got lost after being kidnapped.
name: Everyday Life with D

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 芽衣子のおいしいレストラン (Meiko no Oishī Resutoran)

Shingo, on furlough from the prison, meets a girl named Anzu at the arcade in town. When Gakuto turns to his Guan Yu figurine for guidance, the tip of his sword falls off, starting a chain of events with momentous consequences.
name: Meiko's Delicious Restaurant

description:
Proper Japanese Title: アンドレの日記 (Andore no Nikki)

Andre suffers a mental collapse when he goes for a week without receiving any discipline. Shingo takes Anzu to the movies, but finds his expectations betrayed. The Underground Student Council moves forward with their DTO project.
name: The Diary of Andre

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 体液がいっぱい (Taieki ga Ippai)

Shingo realizes that he saw emails regarding DTO on the computer in the corrections office, which if recovered by the boys, would prove that they were set up. The boys plot to break into the corrections office.
name: Full of Bodily Fluids

description: Proper Japanese Title: 揚げたアスパラガス串
name: Deep-Fried Asparagus Skewers

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺のものがたり (Ore no Monogatari)

Gouda Takeo is a first-year high school student. Clocking in at 2 meters and 120 kilos, Takeo is a socially awkward hothead who's straight as an arrow. One day, he saves a high school girl from a groper on a train, and falls in love with her the next day when she comes by to thank him. But he believes that she must have fallen instead for his best friend with model-like good looks...
name: My Story

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺の恋 (Ore no Koi)

Takeo and Yamato are now text pals. Takeo's heart skips a beat every time he gets a girly text from Yamato, but he believes Yamato has fallen for Suna and vows to make her dream come true.
name: My Romance

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺の青鬼 (Ore no Ao Oni)

Takeo and Yamato finally meet alone. Although Takeo had thought that Yamato just wanted some relationship advice for approaching Sunakawa, Takeo is taken aback when Yamato starts crying.
name: My Blue Ogre

description:
Proper Japanese Title: うちの彼氏 (Uchi no Kareshi)

Yamato's crush wasn't Sunakawa, but Takeo! Elated by having a girlfriend for the very first time, Takeo's heart is about to burst from happiness. But Takeo's true mettle is about to be tested when a major accident occurs during a singles meetup between his and Yamato's friends...
name: My Boyfriend

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺はニブイ (Ore wa Nibui)

Ai, Sunakawa's sister three years his senior, is shocked to learn during a home visit that Takeo is dating. Having secretly harbored feelings of her own for Takeo, Ai is suspicious of Takeo's girlfriend and launches her own investigation...
name: I'm Dense

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺のねがい (Ore no Negai)

Now that he has a girlfriend for the first time in his life, Takeo has been treating Yamato with kid gloves. But Yamato's been acting unhappy of late, which leads Ai to believe that Yamato's hiding something from Takeo. What is Yamato's secret, and what will Ai do once she finds out what it is...?
name: My Wish

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺の強さ (Ore no Tsuyosa)

Takeo's asked by senpais in a Judo club to join them and participate in a match against their rivals, the Bianka High School Judo Club, a month later. Takeo agrees right away, and trains furiously as Yamato cheers him on. Will he win?
name: My Strength

description: When an alien race begs the Avengers to save them from mysterious invaders, the team discovers Thanos is plundering the planet. Meanwhile, Tony seeks new challenges for the team.
name: New Frontiers

description:
Proper Japanese Title: なかなか面白い人間達 (Nakanaka Omoshiroi Ningen-tachi)

The Student Cultural Society experiences problems of an out-of-body sort….and it’s getting worse! The group is at an absolute loss until a mysterious figure explains everything…well, almost everything!
name: Some Fascinating Humans

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ジョバーとローブロー (Jobā to Rōburō)

As the body switching becomes more common place, the Student Cultural Society members become more adventurous with each other’s body.
name: Jobber and Low Blow

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 二つの想い (Futatsu no Omoi)

Inaban is not well, and she has been hiding it from the group. Taichi, who has literally walked in her shoes…and body for that matter…has felt her physical pain and is determined to help her.
name: Twin Feelings

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ある告白、そして死は… (Aru Kokuhaku, Soshite Shi wa...)

Heartseed has grown bored with the group. For a change of pace, he takes over Iori’s body and jumps off a bridge.
name: A Confession and a Death...

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 気づいた時にはまた始まっていたという話 (Kizuita Toki ni wa Mata Hajimatteita toiu Hanashi)

After weeks of blissful silence, the members of the group have started hearing voices, and once again their peace has been shattered.
name: A Story That Continued Before Anyone Realized It

description:
Proper Japanese Title: バラバラと崩れる (Barabara to Kuzureru)

Acting on your desires can be nice. But when members of the Student Council do so, momentary pleasure might cause permanent damage.
name: Falling Apart

description:
Proper Japanese Title: そして誰もいなくなった (Soshite Dare mo Inakunatta)

The quarrels between club members is causing a mighty rift to form between them all until they receive some surprisingly good advice from an unlikely source. All the infighting between the club members is beginning the boil over.
name: And Then There Were None

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 止まらない止まらない止まらない (Tomaranai Tomaranai Tomaranai)

Inaba is the only member of the group who can't seem to be honest about her desires.
name: Can't Stop, Can't Stop, Can't Stop

description:
Proper Japanese Title: それを言葉にするということ (Sore o Kotoba ni Suru toiu Koto)

Heartseed's warning that he will make things interesting begins to come to fruition. To avoid becoming a cautionary tale, Inaba and Iori vow to leave someone crying.
name: Putting Into Words

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 気づきを与えられて始まったという話 (Kizuki o Ataerarete Hajimatta toiu Hanashi)

Heartseed's absence has allowed the group to enjoy some time off; but Taichi soon receives a visitor who will stir up new troubles.
name: A Story That Began As We Realized It

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 雪降る街へ (Yuki Furu Machi e)

While Kiriyama deals with a friend from the best and the promise she can’t remember. Aoki must decide who he really loves.
name: Into a Snowy City

description:
Proper Japanese Title: この五人がいれば (Kono Gonin ga Ireba)

Everyone pays the price for Taichi's mistake. Later, Iori receives a call from her mother, and the team sets out to help.
name: As Long as the Five of Us are Together

description: Proper Japanese Title: 壊れてゆく日々 (Kowareteyuku Hibi)
name: The Days Fall Apart

description: Proper Japanese Title: なにも見えてない　なにもわかってない (Nanimo Mietenai Nanimo Wakattenai)
name: You Don't See It, You Don't Get It

description: Proper Japanese Title: 覚悟と氷解 (Kakugo to Hyōkai)
name: Determination and Resolution

description: Proper Japanese Title: 覚悟と氷解 (Kokoro o Tsunaide)
name: Connecting Hearts

description:
Proper Japanese Title: オレのトモダチ (Ore no Tomodachi)

Yamato's birthday is fast approaching, and Takeo plans out their birthday date with Suna's help. Sensing something amiss with Suna, Yamato suggests inviting Suna to their date, but Suna says that he has something he needs to do that day...
name: My Friend

description:
Proper Japanese Title: オレとトモダチ (Ore to Tomodachi)

Yamato's birthday is the same day Suna's father is scheduled to undergo surgery. Takeo tries to honor Suna's wishes by following through with his and Yamato's birthday date, but Takeo can't stop thinking about Suna's plight. After much thought, Takeo decides to tell Yamato...
name: My Friend and I

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺の山 (Ore no Yama)

Takeo and Yamato head off to a mountain to have a picnic, but they lose their way. Takeo decides that his mission is to get Yamato home safe and sound, but Yamato's only thought is about how they have to spend the night together. Will they be able to return alive?
name: My Mountain

description: After they escape a riot, Travis, Liza and Chris seek refuge with the Salazars; Madison defends her home.
name: The Dog

has_staff_review.name: Fear the Walking Dead Episode #103: "The Dog"

description: Madison and Travis see different sides of the National Guard's occupation in their neighborhood; the family tries to adapt to the new world.
name: Not Fade Away

has_staff_review.name: Fear The Walking Dead Episode #104: "Not Fade Away"

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 素晴らしき尻哉、人生！

The boys are resigned to their upcoming expulsions, and spirits are low, until Gakuto, suffering a bout of temporary insanity, devises one last strategy to get them out of their predicament, if they can just buy enough time to pull it off.
name: It's a Bum-derful Life

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ?

Wakako eats hokke.
name: Hokke

description: When Coulson and the team discover a new Inhuman, S.H.I.E.L.D. comes face to face with another organization searching for powered people. And still reeling from Simmons' dramatic disappearance, Fitz goes to extreme lengths to try to learn how to get her back.
name: Laws of Nature

has_staff_review.name: Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. Episode 301: "Laws of Nature"

deck: Steven and Connie sneak into a hospital to recover Rose's Sword.
name: Nightmare Hospital

deck: Steven helps Sadie plan a performance for Beach-a-Palooza.
name: Sadie's Song

series.name: My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic

description: Proper Japanese Title: 聖騎士の白き柔肌に迫る獣欲の罠 (Hijiri kishi no shiroki yawahada ni semaru jūyoku no wana)
name: A Snare To Trap A Pure Maiden

description:
Proper Japanese Title: うまるとお兄ちゃん (Umaru to Onii-chan)

Umaru reads manga, talks to a hamster, shows off how much of a good girl she is at school, and goes shopping with Onii-chan and stuff!
name: Umaru and Onii-chan

description:
Proper Japanese Title: デュラハンのいる日常 (Durahan no Iru Nichijō)

Unable to stand watching Kimihito and the monster girls go on dates every day, the MON members decide to go on fake dates with him. As Kimihito has a pleasant time with the girls who show him parts of their personality they normally keep hidden, a figure thought to be the culprit approaches them directly!
name: Everyday Life with a Dullahan

description: Proper Japanese Title: モンスター娘たちのいる日常 (Monsutā Musume-tachi no Iru Nichijō)
name: Everyday Life with Monster Girls

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 転校生が来た (Tenkōsei ga Kita)

A new student arrives in a small school in the country, where there are only 5 other students, and they all share the same class.
name: A Transfer Student Arrived

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺の海 (Ore no Umi)

Summer means going to the beach! Takeo and Yamato's crew get together for a beach outing. Always dazzled by Takeo's superhuman abilities, Yamato's plan is to set Takeo's heart a-flutter with her swimsuit, but will it result in anything more?
name: My Ocean

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺の偏差値 (Ore no Hensachi)

When Yamato makes an offhand comment that she'd like the two of them to go to the same university, it motivates Takeo to study like his life depends on it. But Yamato's first choice school is Murasakifuji, a top university. Takeo crams in preparation for a benchmark exam to figure out his chances for getting in, but will he make the cut?
name: My Grades

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 今日は俺のおごりだ (Kyō wa Ore no Ogori da)

Ore 13: One day, Okada meets pretty boy Oda. He'd been rejected by Sunakawa's sister Ai, and he wanted to have a word with Takeo, who was the cause of his rejection.
name: Today Is on Me

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺のジンクス (Ore no Jinkusu)

Takeo and Yamato end up going to MM Land with Ai, Oda, and Suna. While the two enjoy the various attractions of MM Land, Oda tries everything in his power to have Takeo and Ai have a moment alone together in the hopes that Ai can confess her longtime feelings to Takeo. Will Ai do it?
name: My Jinx

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺の彼女 (Ore no Kanojo)

Saijou Mariya, a classmate of Takeo's, would not count running as one of her favorite activities, but she ends up being assigned to a relay at the school festival along with Takeo. Takeo tries to help Saijou improve through practice. Saijou, who barely knows Takeo, gradually comes to realize his rare qualities...
name: My Girlfriend

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺の弟子 (Ore no Deshi)

Saijou Mariya tells Takeo that she likes him "as a person" after falling for Takeo, knowing full well that he already has a girlfriend. Being dense, Takeo takes her words literally, but what will he do once he finds out how she really feels?
name: My Disciple

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺のクリスマス (Ore no Kurisumasu)

Takeo and Yamato's friends get together for a Christmas party. Takeo's friend, Kurihara, reveals that he intends to ask Nanako out, but his numerous faux pas turn Nanako off. As the party draws to an awkward close, no one knows what will happen...
name: My Christmas

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺の誕生日 (Ore no Tanjōbi)

Takeo's long-awaited birthday has finally arrived. Yamato really wants to make it a memorable one by attempting a first kiss. But Takeo's obliviousness may ruin everything...
name: My Birthday

description: Spider-Man's dream of joining the Avengers becomes a nightmare when Loki switches bodies with the web: slinger, turning his new teammates against him.
name: The Avenging Spider-Man, Part One
